$ and the degree of rotational support also resemble\nobservations. The lowest-mass UFDs are below surface brightness limits of\ncurrent surveys but are potentially visible in next-generation surveys (e.g.\nLSST). The stellar metallicities are lower than in LG dwarfs; this may reflect\npre-enrichment of the LG by the massive hosts or Pop-III stars. Consistency\nwith lower resolution studies implies that our simulations are numerically\nrobust (for a given physical model).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Dec 2018 19:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-23"}
